{"word":"τρύξ","slug":"τρύξ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τρύξ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>akin to <a href='S:τρύγη'><el>τρύγη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>new wine not yet fermented, wine with the lees in it, must</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>mustum</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the lees of wine</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>faex</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of <i>an old man</i> or <i>woman</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}